Cell.Text: G|Yes, youngling. Have a seat.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakIntroBranchTopic: You wished to see me?

Cell.Text: Your hearts are full of grief, and my own weeps at the loss of Skjor. | But his death was avenged long ago. You have taken more lives than honor demanded. | The cycle of retaliation may continue for some time.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakPlayerSpillTheBeans: Aela and I work to avenge Skjor's death.

Cell.Text: Lad, I know what you've been up to.
Lass, I know what you've been up to.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakPlayerTriesToHideIt: I work for the honor of the Companions.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Talos guide you, lad.
[S] G|Talos guide you, lass.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakSeeYa: It will be done.

Cell.Text: Mind you, it's no business of mine what each Companion does in the name of honor. | But this sneaking around. It doesn't befit warriors of your standing. Aela knows better, and so should you.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakPlayerTriesToHideContinuation

Cell.Text: [S] In any case, I have a task for you.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakContinuation

Cell.Text: Have you heard the story of how we came to be werewolves?

Node.Caption: C04KodlakGiveTaskTopic: You said you had a task for me?

Cell.Text: Aye, that sounds like him. | As in all matters of faith, though, the reality is more complicated than one believer would tell you.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakILessThanThreeWerewolves: Skjor said it was a blessing from Hircine.

Cell.Text: The boy has a nugget of truth, but the reality is more complicated than that. | It always is.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakBadDog: Vilkas said it was a curse laid upon the ancient Companions.

Cell.Text: The Companions are nearly five thousand years old. This matter of beastblood has only troubled us for a few hundred. | One of my predecessors was a good, but short-sighted man. He made a bargain with the witches of Glenmoril Coven. | If the Companions would hunt in the name of their lord, Hircine, we would be granted great power.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakTruthAboutDogs: So what is the truth, then?

Cell.Text: They did not believe the change would be permanent. The witches offered payment, like anyone else. | But we had been deceived.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakPowerDescribe: And they became werewolves?

Cell.Text: [S] The witches didn't lie, of course. But it's more than our bodies.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakButILikeWerewolves: But aren't you more powerful now?

Cell.Text: [S] We'll get to that. | It's not so simple as just killing them, though.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakSonOfAWitch: The witches should be hunted down for their trickery.

Cell.Text: Ah yes, their trickery.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakReallyGiveTaskTopic: You were telling me about the witches.

Cell.Text: The disease, you see, affects not just our bodies. It seeps into the spirit. | Upon death, werewolves are claimed by Hircine for his Hunting Grounds. | For some, this is a paradise. They want nothing more than to chase prey with their master for eternity. | And that is their choice. But I am still a true Nord. And I wish for Sovngarde as my spirit home.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakBodyToSoul

Cell.Text: [S] That's what I've spent my twilight years trying to find out. | And now I've found the answer. The witches' magic ensnared us, and only their magic can release us. | They won't give it willingly, but we can extract their foul powers by force. | I want you to seek them out. Go to their coven in the wilderness. Strike them down as a true warrior of the wild. | And bring me their heads. The seat of their abilities. From there, we may begin to undo centuries of impurity.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakIsThereACure: Is there a way to cure yourself?

Cell.Text: You shall have no Shield-Brother this time. But the spirit of Ysgramor goes with you, to restore the honor of his legacy.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakJustMeQuestionMark: Am I to do this alone?

Cell.Text: Good. Now move quickly. And don't leave any of them alive.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakImOnIt: It shall be done.

Cell.Text: This is not about your desires, lad.
This is not about your desires, lass.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakIWantToBeAWerewolf: I don't wish to remove this blessing.

Cell.Text: What is this about?
I hear you've been busy of late.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakUhOhHeKnows

Cell.Text: G|Your own fate will be your own choice. Just as always. | Now be gone.

Node.Caption: C04KodlakNoFateButWhatWeMake
